SUMMARY:Fools Moon Hike
DESCRIPTION:Bring a flashlight and your sense of wonder as you explore the park after dark this April Fools’ day. This hike heads up to the summit of Bald Mountain\, where we will see the moon rise over the Mayacamas and the sun set over Sonoma Valley. This is a strenuous hike of approximately 6.5 miles with 1500+ of vertical and some steep sections (not recommended for children under 12). \nMeet at the White Barn parking lot at least 10 minutes prior to the start time. Tickets are $10 general or $5 for youth (12-17 year olds)\, students\, Sugarloaf members\, and Sugarloaf and RFO volunteers. All minors must be accompanied by a parent or legal guardian. You must register on this page to attend; tickets will not be available on site. Bring your flashlight\, at least a quart of water\, snacks\, and extra layers for the evening. Parking fees apply.
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/fools-moon-hike/
LOCATION:Sugarloaf Ridge State Park\, 2605 Adobe Canyon Rd\, Kenwood\, CA
CATEGORIES:Recreation
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://golocal.coop/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Full-moon-hike-sugarloaf-2s-xcBrom.jpg
GEO:38.4427;-122.533
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Sugarloaf Ridge State Park 2605 Adobe Canyon Rd Kenwood CA;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=2605 Adobe Canyon Rd:geo:-122.533,38.4427
END:VEVENT
